OL,3,CDFDS Seaways apologise after
OL,4,Cwheelchair user left in their van
OL,5,Cduring crossing
OL,7,FJersey's Economic Development Minister
OL,8,Fsays it's unacceptable that a
OL,9,Fwheelchair user had to remain in their
OL,10,Fvan during a DFDS Seaways ferry
OL,11,Fcrossing to Poole.
OL,13,FDeputy Kirsten Morel was responding to
OL,14,Fan urgent question from Deputy
OL,15,FMontfort Tadier about the incident.
OL,17,FDeputy Tadier said the "harrowing"
OL,18,Fcase involved James Thompson, who was
OL,19,Fobliged to stay in his vehicle
OL,20,Fthroughout the sailing to Poole.
