OL,3,CDFDS Seaways apologise after
OL,4,Cwheelchair user left in their van
OL,5,Cduring crossing
OL,7,F"However, as the passenger needed to
OL,8,Fbe in the UK that evening to connect
OL,9,Fwith another journey, he chose to
OL,10,Fcontinue the scheduled departure,
OL,11,Ffully aware that he would need to
OL,12,Fremain on the car deck for the
OL,13,Fcrossing.
OL,15,F"A member of DFDS staff stayed with
OL,16,Fhim throughout the journey to provide
OL,17,Fsupport.
